# Nairly API — project overview

This is the **standalone REST API backend** for the Nairly event-planning marketplace (Mongolia-focused). It is a separate deployment from the frontend(s) and is consumed by:

- `event-planning` — Next.js customer/provider frontend
- `event-planning-admin` — admin dashboard (separate project)
- Future: mobile app

## Stack

- **Runtime**: Node.js (tsx for dev, compiled JS for prod)
- **Framework**: [Hono](https://hono.dev) — lightweight, TypeScript-first HTTP framework
- **Database**: Supabase (PostgreSQL) via `@supabase/supabase-js`
- **Validation**: Zod + `@hono/zod-validator`
- **Auth**: Supabase JWT — verified server-side on every protected request

## Project structure

```
src/
  index.ts              ← app entry, CORS, global error handler, port 4000
  types/index.ts        ← AuthUser, Hono ContextVariableMap extension
  lib/
    supabase.ts         ← service-role client (bypasses RLS) + per-user scoped client
  middleware/
    auth.ts             ← authenticate, requireAdmin, requireProvider
  routes/
    venues.ts           ← public + provider venue CRUD + availability
    orders.ts           ← authenticated checkout + user order list/detail
    categories.ts       ← category catalog
    time-slots.ts       ← per-venue weekly pricing config
    admin/
      orders.ts         ← admin: all orders, stats, status changes
      providers.ts      ← admin: provider list, verify, role management
```

## Base URL

- Dev: `http://localhost:4000`
- Prod: `https://api.nairly.mn` (or your deployment URL)

## Domain model (Supabase tables)

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `venues` | Venue listings with capacity, pricing, location |
| `categories` | Venue type catalog (slug-based) |
| `venue_time_slots` | Weekly day-of-week pricing overrides per venue |
| `orders` | Customer checkout orders |

## Roles (stored in `app_metadata.role`)

- `customer` — browse and book
- `provider` — manage own venues and time slots (requires admin verification)
- `admin` — full access including user management
